The paper deals with the problem of secure caching, which involves both information theory and network security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication systems. The paper also involves network security, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper discusses the problem of minimizing information leakage to an external wiretapper, which falls under the category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves designing content placement and delivery mechanisms, which suggests the category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the tradeoff between cache memory and transmission rate, which falls under the category cs.SY (Systems and Control).
